review.text: Bestest oldest authentic Chinese food , must go place

Want to have tasty Chinese and Japanese food? Then try FUJIYA in Chanakyapuri, tried hot and sour and corn soup followed by chilly potato, mojito, spring rolls and after that pan fried noodles with gravy. Delicious food was served and the staff was also polite and respectful, amazing experience at this place. Will visit this place again with my friends.

Fujiya is listed in the legendary restaurants of Delhi.It has been here since decades and I had high expectations from this place.They had a vast menu with a lot of dishes.So we decided to order a veg Sushi platter and pan friend noodles. Their pan fried looked very different than the ones I am used to eating.The noodles were fried,more like choupsey and topped with lots of veggies and greens.The sauce of the veggies was bland,some translucent kind of sauce with no flavours just basic salt and pepper.So the noodles were very disappointing.I have had far better pan fried at other places! Next the sushi also couldn’t impress.Tempura sushi was still ok considering the other ones.Other sushi we didn’t took even a second serving after trying it.We unfortunately couldn’t even finish our meals and left!
The food is as chinjabi as possible. It’s just because of the old school feel you can go to the place.
We ordered sushi, fried rice, chili garlic noodles and Hong Kong chicken. Food was pathetic. Completely not worth going. Strictly a NO NO NO NO NO N if u tell them about it , no body bothers.

Lost charm. Very bad experience both in food & service. Had gone with family for lunch. 1. Hot & sour chicken soup was tasteless neither spicy not tasty. 2. Chilli garlic noodles had hardly and garlic & was bland. 3. Prawns in hot garlic sauce was like a below average Indian curry with prawns thrown in it. Horrible taste. When I called manager Thakur he was rude and said it is cooked this way only. Anyways had such a bad experience that wanted to make others aware.
Not a good place for chatore indians. then they have their own order of charging service charge which is a obove the Hon'ble Supreme Court.
Never go there

A lovely restaurant with good ambience. Chilly fish tastes awesome. Must try for all. One of the places to find authentic Chinese soup. I tried Hot&Sour Chicken soup , chili garlic noodles and chicken in hot garlic sauce. Retreat for Chinese people in Delhi 。 。 。 。 。 会 Thumps Up !

Having turned down a couple of times due to a full house, I decided to visit on a Tuesday (when everyone turns vegetarian) evening. Got a warm welcome with a choice of tables even! But in a few minutes, as we were about to dig into our soup, the place was bustling with people waiting outside. So, what’s the fuss all about? It’s the old world feel. It gives you a feeling that it’s been there since ages with a tribe of loyal customers. It’s like nothing has changed and that’s what people love about it. It isn’t cheap by any standards but I guess it’s a great place to grab a beer and munch on an appetiser. A big bottle of Kingfisher is for 300/- . Food: well, it’s nothing special but you can’t fault it. And that’s what brings people back here. You just can’t go wrong. They offer an array of Chinese and Japanese dishes. Some indian dishes quietly slipped in like Gobi Manchurian 😜 I tried the corn and asparagus soup, the chilly baby corn, aromatic pork dumplings, Japanese sticky rice with vegetables. Everything was just right. Right amount of spice, right portion size, fresh ingredients. Quite a homely feel to the place. And the decor coupled with the bustle of the place makes for a good happy outing. Worth a try.

All time favorite place for me to have such a delicious food of my taste. Love this place food with it's vast options cable to fulfill your empty belly. Service is too fast ambience also soo good. Love it Instagram {uid:38945158}

Like the place to have the oriental cuisine. I went to this place with my wife and my daughter. We ordered Chicken Spring Roll: They are crunchy and good option for a starter. Spicy Stir Fry French Beans: Crisp yet not overcooked with the right amount of favoring and went perfectly with the fried rice Zha Jiang noodles: This was the star. Perfect Chinese dish consisting of thick wheat noodles topped with Zhejiang sauce. For drinks, we had virgin Mohito. It was refreshing as it should be. For desserts, We had Brownie zebra: Perfect dessert to satisfy your sweet truth. The service was quick and attentive. I will visit here again.

The ambience of CP’s Berco’s is apparently very appealing. Love the decor. Perfect date place for chinese lovers. I’m a huge fan of their chilli garlic vegetables, the authentic chinese taste. ️ But they really lack in honey chilli potatoes. It either feels too soggy and sweet, or it feels overcooked. I tried it 3 different times but I don’t feel it was a mistake, that is their fixed recipe and it tastes like a sweet dish to me. Service is great here!

I went to cp with my friends fir some party. I saw this outlet of bercos and decided to do a takeaway of some food fir my family. I ordered crispy corn, chilli potatoes, cheese and corn along with a different dish which called sanghai style rice and noodles. Coming to the first, corn were really nice nad crisp with perfect flavours balanced. Chilli potatoes had a nice tangy flavour which made it taste good. Coming to the cheese rolls, they went a little soggy after it was packet but still it was really cheesyyy i must say! , the mixed noodels and too tasted different i would say, ut was something i had never tried before! Overall a nice experience.

1. Ordered Prawn Tom Yum Soup, Black Pepper Chicken Dimsums and Garlic & Cheese Wontons. 2. The Tom Yum Soup was excellent with sufficient prawns and the perfect combination of tangy and spicy. 3. The Chicken Dimsums were great with the Garlic & Cheese Wontons being even better. 4. Orders are served reasonably fast. 5. Pricing could have been a bit more reasonable.

The board looks very basic on the outside, but the restaurant interiors are absolutely amazing 😍. Tried the 'Chicken Tom Kha' and 'Veg Wonton Soup' which were both amazing. Had the 'Honey Chilli Potatoes' sans the honey, which was perfect, crisp and spicy. The only disappointment was the 'Chicken Pan Fried Noodles'. The dish was way too oily and the pan frying wasn't done well, hence the crust wasn't formed perfectly and the noodles weren't as crispy at the bottom. The service was a tad bit too slow and very disorganized. They brought in the appetizer before the soup which was very weird. The pricing was perfect though. So overall, would definitely recommend 👍.

No doubt in excellent staff service. Delicious servings and perfect ambience for dine out with family or couple. Best view at corner tables of stairs (Those who are fond of selfies) It is pocket friendly too. Make sure to order their thai rice bowl (Damn delicious) if you are going for heavy meal. Meal.for 2 in 1000 bucks

Ordered their Three Pepper Bowl which is usually my go to dish. Instead of their noodles, I went for the rice. The only thing I didn’t like about the dish was ‘the quantity of the gravy& Amount of grilled chicken they had put in. I couldn’t complete my rice with it. Had to borrow some spoons of my friend’s Grilled fish in order to eat it all. Though I liked the ambiance, Liked the co-operative staff. 😀
Let the Christmas charm die a Death with Chocolate topping over the Christmas Spirit ✨

If I had to rate just on ambience, I would have given this place 5 star. Such a beautiful place it is. Food is good too but a little bit costly. We ordered Veg Spring Roll and Cold Coffee. Spring Roll tasted good. Not worth the price though. Cold Coffee was okayish. I'll recommend this place just for the look and feel it projects.

Colonel’s Kababz in Defence Colony, New delhi has been doing kebabs and curries since about 25 years now and their quality of food is definitely premium. In the picture: Gosht Seekh Kebab (Colonel’s Special) The kebabs were succulent with amazing mutton blend which is very juicy and moist and the chuntey served along went very well with these but I found the kebabs to be a little overpriced, maybe because of the brand name associated to it, the quantity and presentation could be better. @colonels.kababz @colonels_kababz
Food was good but too much salt in the preli dal tarka. so pls just put less salt. because we can alwz add more but cant redduce the salt pls
Very juicy mutton seekh kabab @colonel kabab defence colonel delhi

Rolls are OVER PRIC3D Rs. 200 and are tasteless. Upon complaining staff said 'we find it Ok'. :/ Menu on tomato has different and lower pricing. The menu given this is attached as a pic. Very bad experience

Although its a old and "Supposedly" a legendary place, tried a Lehsuni Chicken tikka. I Visited the DefCol market itself after ages and really thought of relieving old memories by having their tikka. Unfortunately it was really not upto the taste as it used to be long time back and paying more than 500 bucks for it really hurts.

The Pinner tikka roll was pathetic as it was stale and dry. Paneer was way too hard and it was smelling The green chutney was so bad, it made me puke. It was stinking and had a sour taste. The onions were yellow and stale For 200 rs for a roll, they should at least maintain some hygiene, just because they sit in defence market, doesn’t mean they can sell anything Colonels has rightly lost its charm

I have been to this place once. We ordered chicken tikka roll which was fresh and tasty. In main course we tried Chicken bhayankar which is their speciality. The preparation was good. I liked the quality of chicken they use. The tandoori roti was crispy and the rumali roti was perfectly cooked. Overall I liked their food. The prices are on little higher side. The service is good and quick.

The place is easy to locate but once you get there and order food that is where you start to get disappointed, the sizes of each portion are very small and do not provide enough value for the money that is being paid। Rating: Taste 6/10 Service 6/10 (just because they bring the food till your car) Value for money 2/10

Well this place is overpriced and the food is highly overrated. Spent quite a lot of money for nothing and honestly speaking what’s the price for ? Very very disappointed would suggest people to go to Al Nawaz or other restaurants that are far better than this place. Thank you.

Ever since the seating has been sealed , this outdoor serving restaurant has gone to the dogs and quite literally . From being my favourite go to place for Kebabs ever since I was a kid it has now become a place which has the worst possible service levels and poor hygiene. With barely 3 outdoor high tables ( and about 5 cars in which people drink and eat ) , the serving staff is rude and disrespects patrons . The serving time for orders has increased surprisingly as they are focusing more on the delivery business . A terrible experience . Would not recommend to anyone looking for a pleasant experience .

When I first saw the facade of this place I was awestruck and knew I had to check this place out. After entering I didn't wanted to leave this place anytime soon. The interior is just beautiful. I ordered their "Chilly Garlic Prawns". The presentation was really nice and it was a delight to eat. The flavours were balanced and every flavour was distinct. Really amazing place to chill.

The ambience of this place is too attractive to see. Chilli basil cottage cheese is too good of this place . It had ample of sitting area, which is comfortable too. The staff members of this place take care of each and every need of the customers taste and preference. I liked this place a lot.

I had visited to this place yesterday in the evening to have a delicious food here. The ambience of this place is too good to see. There was polite and alert staff here. Here i had tried: Chilli garlic lotus root Orange chilli prawns Fluffy steamed rice Kung bao chicken All the food stuff was too delectable special the orange chilli prawns. The quality of the food was upto the mark. HIGHLY RECOMMEND
Regular run of the mill buffet food. Taste wise it was OK but not there to beat some good food The drinks with buffet are just one per person which is a let down

I had been to this place with my friends to have some Chinese cuisine. First of all soups and salad varieties was damn good. It has a great ambience. Indoor sitting area is simple fabulous. Staff is very friendly and courteous. Service was prompt. We had ordered Chilli Honey Potato Veg Spring Roll Virgin Mojito and Butter Scotch Ice Cream Shake. All the ice-cream shakes and drinks are outstanding. I really like their menu. I really enjoyed over here with my friends and will definitely keep visiting.

This is a dine-in outlet bar. It serves all kinds of Asian, Thai, Chinese and Sea Food. I recently visited this place and ordered some momos from here. They were utterly delicious😋 The service was good and the ambience was great. The price of the dishes were totally worth the taste. J thoroughly enjoyed myself here and will surely recommend this place to everyone!

Has an amazing tune with friends at this fabulous place. Love the decor, ambience, vibes, food and the staff was courteous. The order was served on time. We ordered Fried rice Kind pao chicken 3 spice chicken chilli honey potato All these dishes are a must try for all the foodies out there📍 Highly recommended , with great decor and really yummy dishes that too at affordable prices❤

This is really good place to have food from the food is really good the taste is yummy the quality is really good to have food was very yummy and delicious the delivery was done on time food was very tasty and delicious the packing was very good and safe had drums of heaven and drunken chicken which was very good to have over all good experience of ordering food from here a must try place

We were looking for a place to visit in the evening a few days ago, then we found this restaurant named Drums of heaven and visited this restaurant. This place is quite famous for it's food. We did lunch here. The food here is very good. Drums of heaven and chillli potatoes are a must try.

Recently visited this place and it was really a great visit. Environment is really healthy and positive. For me it was totally worth it. Staff was really nice. And services are appreciated. And food was very yum and tasty. Ordered: drums soya chilli Hot dragon chicken and honey chilli chicken. And along with them cold coffee. 5/5 to their food. mouth drooling! Highly recommend place!
Nice place. Kind of a vintage feel to it. Dal gosht was nice. Tandoori platter can be tried.

I had my eyes on this place since i was a child roaming the streets of Cannught Place. Finally visited last week. Experience was good. Food tasted average. Nothing to draw myself back. Staff is friendly thought. I liked paneer tikka more than chiken malai tikka. Butter Chicken was debated though - it is not as sweet as some people prefer.

We were shopping at connaught place and were looking to eat at a good place, we spotted embassy and entered. They have a seating capacity of close to 80-90 people on the ground n first floor. A well stocked bar too. We ordered paneer pakodas , masala papad , half butter chicken ,and a few tandoori rotis. Damages to the pocket - Rs 1528 ( US $ 21.4 ) inclusive of all taxes. Overall experience - Rs 650 we paid for half a portion of butter chicken was cut throat , just too expensive and the taste was nothing great. I would rate this place 3 on 5
I have gone with my family ,it wasa great experience and specially the famous daal makani daal I like so much and mushroom was the great ,nice presentation by the staff.
Visited the place for lunch with a friend. We ordered tandoori veg platter, the food was impressive. And the ambience was nice, vintage and fancy.
Cream of tomato soup. Here the beauty is the tomatoes are well well mixed which a wonderful taste of typical tomato soup with cream topping and bread crunch.
Great food and service loved the channa bhatora. Took my foreign clients and they had a great time. Thanks to Mr Pandey and Mr Deepak for giving us a great experience
I love all of its snacks: Big Samosa Large Bread pakora Veg. Hot dog Paneer patty And their mint sauce👌
Please donot waste your money by going to such restaurants. Even after replacing the first one the second one was terrible.

Great place ! lovely food ! Fine dining at Connaught Place . Lip smacking Indian food. We tried the masala papad, paneer pakoda, it was melting in the mouth .butter chicken was great but could have been boneless . Overall a great experience !

FAIYAN - The Chinese restaurant in Middle circle, Connaught Place!❤ . So i visited this place with my family on weekend and I really love the Chinese there. Basically, we were craving for Chinese cusine from very long time and at good location! So we found this one at CP and what could be better than Connaught Place. We had chop suey, fried rice, schezwan noodles and schezwan chilli paneer!🤤 It was a drooling experience for us and we came back home burping and my happy face!😌 Do visit and have some amazing chinese there!😍 We spent around 1200 rupees for 4 people!🤑

Small yet cosy. My favorite was their freshly brewed artisanal coffee. I went looking for something light but filling and got myself some talumein. I think the taste was on point. I wish I could take home their super beautiful crockeries.

Worst part was they don't accept card payments. But cleared the same while placing the order. We ordered Hotn sour soup, pineapple rice and prawn on both the dishes main ingredients was missing (prawns and pineapple) was missing. It was such disaster to went this place. But ambience was good and relaxing. I suggest other place over this restaurant which is far better.

A very small and compact place but food is awesome , you can feel the freshness and aroma of the food very well , potato toastier, chilli garlic noodles , veg manchurian must try, the ice cream they serve is less sugary and simply great, a must visit
The food was tasty with authentic chinese flavours. The staff was courteous and the place was not to noisy, good for an quiet evening time .

Thus is in strict sense a restaurant only , no interiors or things to look at . But wat they believe in is good food n service n m glad to have tried this . Had booked it b4 but I was d only customer , may b the navratre effect ! Talunein soup was really good , d best I ever had , especially for the thin noodles in it . admixed with gentle amount of assorted veggies . D best part is " spring rolls" , I would die for them . So good was the exterior coating , not too thick or thin n no oil coming out n smearing my hands ! Filled with cabbage onion mix , fried to just the optimum level. a must try . , do try the red sauce with it , we used it to garnish our other item tooo. Next up , in main course , American choupsey was nothing like I had in so many Chinese joints ! Liquid veggies tomato sauce came separately with the thin noodles . n u mix n eat , it was simply heaven . a go ahead any day . A hidden gem , but definitely needs to work upon the interiors n the wall paints n old serving glasses !

This spot has the best chinese nourishment in focal delhi. Yummy Chinese nourishment and spending cordial! The amount of nourishment per plate is additionally lovely good.We had Honey Chilly Potato, Hakka Noodle and more. All the nourishment was great and superb and they constantly dazzled me by their food.I love the nourishment here.

This place has the best chinese food in central delhi. I love their prawn noodles a lot. The quantity of food is also good. It is very cosy place with very less tables.I would recommend it to anyone looking to eat authentic chinese in a decent budget.

We went to this place for the first time yesterday for a rakhi dinner. My brother likes chinese food so we did a bit of research before going. The place is a bit small and yesterday being a holiday it was crowded so we had to wait a bit. But once we sat down it was a real treat which followed. We ordered crispy salt and pepper veggies, spring rolls and drums of heaven. Didn't quite like the drums of heaven as it was a bit bland and very dry. The dishes were good. We also had pan fried noodles mixed and fa tuan special fried rice. Portions were great and the taste superb. Even after eating so much we didn't feel stuffed. Food was light and tasty. What we liked most was the similarity in taste with Kolkata Chinese which we miss in Delhi. Service was prompt and efficient. Overall a good experience.
This place serves one of the best dim sums in delhi . Personally in love with their clear soups! Authentic alert! I amma go back their soon!
No chicken, only tofu
Excellent food and huge portions. I have decided to always order from Chungwa for home delivery. Very reasonable too. Thank you Chungwa team
Recently ordered in for 1 portion of chicken talumein soup, and 1 veg talumein. It tastes really nice, but I have had spicier talumein soup from it. Also I found salt to be a little less. :)
Very average food however service is brilliant! I mean too good. for some reason everything just taste same for some reason. I mean its just the same.

cherished the administration and the nourishment was filling. Their segments are extraordinary and I adored the inside. I would prescribe this spot to individuals those things who need to have extraordinary Chinese Food.we requested veg manchurian nippy garlic noodles and seared rice all there were astounding in taste and had a better than average look manchurian was fresh and delicate while noodles however crisp yet were of incredible taste and next singed rice were astonishing had an ideal taste and were cooked appropriately.

Legendary late DC Wong authentic Chinese recipes could be found only at two restaurants in delhi, one at chungwa and Fujiya restaurant at Malcha Marg, Chanakyapuri. I love you guys for being consistent in everything. Loves the foods being ordered. Thubten Khimsar, Malviya Nagar.

I love the food. Food is great! However the service needs to improve. Incase you are still finishing your drink and done with your dinner the waiter might serve the bill and keep on reminding you to pay up.

Poor service, no one to take order. Kept on requesting person to take order. Waited for 20 min only to order. Food was cold, got changed repeat was also cold. Iced tea was syrub. Received each items delayed. Had a very bad experience.

The staff was very bad and not cooperative at all. The chicken was smelling and they were just not ready to accept their mistake.i asked for the manager they were not making me talk to anyone. I can’t believe this type of service. So disappointed I would still expect a call back from the manager so I can actually explain what’s going on in this restaurant.

Visited after long time only to be immensely disappointed! Tried veg wonton soup, chicken in black bean sauce with rice and vegetables in black bean sauce with rice (the meal). Everything was absolutely bland and no taste or texture whatsoever! The prices are relatively high as compared to nearby Asian/Chinese restaurants but the quality was so sad! Never visiting again .
This is a yummy Chinese place where you can satisfy. I am totally love in with vibe of the place. They have some cute crockery and have courteous staff. Must try ︎Chilli chicken ︎hauka noodles

Ichiban is an amazing option when it comes to having lip smacking Chinese and Thai food. This casual dining place serves Chinese, Japanese and Thai cuisine. Place is beautifully done and has warm vibes. Staff is warm and courteous. For appetizers,  I had  honey chilli potato which were crispy with sweet and spicy notes -it will definitely activate your tastebuds. Spring rolls were little oily but tasted good and it paired well with chilly garlic dip. Crispy tangy button mushrooms are definitely worth trying especially for funghi lovers. For main course, I had  Veg manchurian  which was tasty and manchurian balls were soft. Mushroom dimsums were the star dish here.  I would love to recommend it.Thumbs up! Momo lovers should definitely try. I ended my meal with darsan and date pancakes- both these desserts were out of the box and tasted heavenly. Ichiban will certainly hit the spot when you’re looking out for a Chinese meal. Follow my food journey on Instagram- teekhi_mircheee
A great place to have Chinese and Thai food. Easy on your pocket, the service is quick, the staff is courteous and the food is yummy. A must visit for authentic Chinese lovers.
The food is just beyond amazing loved the dumplings, chicken in hot garlic sauce and noodles. The service was on point 😍

Good food, good prices and big portion size. Ichiban has a big menu with something to everyone’s liking and I love the consistency of the food & service. Chilly garlic noodles are my favourite. Being a vegetarian, there are a ton of yummy choices to pick. Paneer satay, spinach and corn are good dishes too.

I love Chinese food with a touch of familiarity and I love the food at Ichiban for the same reason. I have been to this place with my family and we love the food. It’s a cozy restaurant and the food is the real star. The regular stuff like Chilly Chicken, Hakka Noodles, Pad Thai noodles are amazing without being too oily.

There’s something about age old places in Delhi that accentuate the flavours with delicious nostalgia. Ichiban is definitely one such restaurant serving kick ass Asian food, culminated with richness & quality. The menu is vast so it’s hard to pick favourites but I definitely have a few top picks: Chilly Lotus Stem Singapore Prawns Chilly Chicken Pad Thai Noodles They have started doing sushi too which is great. The rolls aren’t overly creamy and are made with fresh seafood. Price point is perfect too cuz portion size is humungous. Check these guys out if you already haven’t. Thank me later.

I use to regularly order soups from ichiban and believe me they are one of the best outlets to try soups from. The prices are okay but the portions are great , a bowl of soup is a meal in itself. Packaging can be improved upon and so is the preparation time.
Nice cozy place for Chinese food. Must have soup here. Quick service. Tasty food. Full filling quantity!
Amazing food, and their service is soo good I mean I usually don’t write reviews but this one deserved one. Its worth the money. Going to be a regular now.

I just loved the ambience and the ethnic south indian setting here. It just complements your meal completely. Food was good too. Their welcome drinks were good. Mysore masala dosa was again something very good. I would highly recommend it. We ordered panchtara uttapam which had 5 different kinds of uttapam most of them were good. Staff was very proffessional and courteous here.
Most authentic south Indian I have ever tasted 😋

Looking for authentic south indian food? This is what we have been missing until now. First experience at Naivedyam and it turned out to be an amazing one. Such courtesy of staff, servers and such a decent crowd. The restaurant takes you to another dimension. Oh the food! Authenticity at its best. Tip- request for gunpowder chutney.

Naivedyam over all 4/5 Best Food - Rasam, Paysam, Sambhar Food tongue tingler - Fried Chilli Ambience - 5/5 Loved the experience and warmth of restaurant special fried chilli is amazing. Paysam that was served with the naivedyam thali was amazing aswell. Will definitely visit again.

We were a group of 13 people and we went to this pure veg South Indian restaurant. We had ordered in bulk, Naivedyam thalis, Mysore masala dosa, paneer masala dosa, Tamarind rice and even Mysore pak. The food is sumptuous and quite filling. The ambience is also very typical South Indian with soothing Carnatic music playing in the background. All in all, this place is a must visit.

This restaurant has become my favourite place for South Indian food! Anyone who loves south Indian food, must visit here! The fast service, quality food, great taste, vintage ambiance & they way they served the food absolutely made me fall in love with this place! I would absolutely rate 10/10 to this place! Must try Mysore masala dosa & Rasam Papad here! Will absolutely recommend to my friends!

Looking for peninsular Indian dish you should visit this place. Even waiter are dressed in South Indian style and they are friendly in nature. Ordered paneer dosa and veg Thali. Both are good taste wise. One should visit if you crave for South Indian dishes

Naivedyam is a good place if you want to have typical south India cuisine. They have the authentic taste. All the food is majorly cooked in coconut oil. They do have a good variety in the menu. Really like their rasam papad and kesari bhaat. Didn't quite like the uttapam and ragi dosa. Service was great! So overall experience - 3.5/5

Food was tasty , fresh.paid almost 300 for the thali - naivedyam thali. they forgot to give kosambari , when I asked about it the guy looked a bit irritated and got me 1tsp of salad in a katori. i feel for this price the food quantity is extremly less especially the rice.
Authentic South Indian flavour and dishes. Must visit. Very warm staff and soothing ambience.

This place is my first love, being a vegetarian it’s hard to find pure veg restaurants that serve food this tasty. It has been at this location since decades and have been maintaining the quality and taste of food without fail. It’s a perfect place for family dinners and is fairly priced as well. I personally love their kababs, paneer tikka, sahi ke kabab and tabdoori pineapple. All of these have a distinct flavour which stands out from other restaurants. Also, their veg thali is something that i order almost always. The dal makhni here is like no other, with perfect spices, consistency and flavour, it is something that you would come back here for, again and again. My mom likes to order masala chaap and paneer lababdaar which is outstanding too. Coming to dessert and drinks, don’t miss their lassi and fruit custard which is absolutely delicious.
I absolutely loved veg Gulati's food it was so good everything was just perfect in taste. staff was so courteous :D had wonderful experience! Good place for vegetarians :D

Veg Gulati:- It was a marvellous experience Going to Veg Gulati restaurant situated in pandara road , ambience was very good there , staff was very courteous and service was very good. Now comes to major part , food that was very good there , especially Malai and Tandoori Chaap , so guys do have a visit to them and try their food.

Went to Veg Gulati with my family friends for a brunch and trust me this place is perfect for all kind of brunch and family dinner. Ambience here is very sober and decent. Talking about the staff, their service was great and on time. We ordered their dahi ke kebab, soyachaap and tandoori mashroom for starter's. Soya chaap were extremely delicious and was very tender in taste. Tandoori mashroom is a highly recommended dish from Gulati- it was well prepared with lots of flavours. In main course we ordered Rajma chawal combo and Mahara thali. My personal favourite dish in main course was Rajma Chawal. In all we had an amazing time here 😊

If you are hard core vegetarian and want to have some delicious vegetarian food, then this is the must visit place. I recently visited this place with my friend and experience here was very amazing. I tried :- > Dahi ke kebab > Galouti kebab * Both were very delicious and has melt in mouth consistency. > I also tried their Maharaja thali - this thali has dal makhani, shahi paneer, diwani handi, rice, raita, dessert and one paratha. The dal makhani and shahi paneer were really delicious. Overall, I really loved this thali and one must should try this 👍 In desserts I had, gulab jamun and ksheeram. Both were supremely delicious 😍 Will definitely visit this place again for sure 👍

Now Pandara Road has a lot of restaurants but when it comes to vegetarian food, veg gulati stands the best in my eyes. I recently went there with a friend of mine and loved the place to bits. I started with a Tandoori platter and a kebab platter and both the platters are to die for. Grilled pineapple, mushrooms, dahi ke kebabs were the best out of both the platters. Further, they have a huge menu with lots of variety of main course dishes. I had Dal Makhani, Veg Biryani , Soya Rara and Palak Kofta and all of them were delicious. If you are coming here don't forget to try their chaap/soya preparations because they are to die for. Palak Kofta is a must try from my side. You can end the meal with ksheeram which is made with carrot, bottle gaurd and almonds. To be honest, bottle gaurd might not sound too appetizing but this dessert was absolutely delicious. (Highly recommended!) I would definitely love to visit the place again for its awesome food. ♥️

Except for the food (which too was not great guns), nothing was anything better than GROSS. Their staff head came to take the order n guess what he din even know all the items in the platter. He just tried to play bluff without bothering about some vegetarian might end up consuming meat. Also, when I requested him to get it replaced, he told me “jo krna hai krlo, me kuch nahi krunga”.

Worst experience in service and food quality. We ordered 6 salads through zomato from this subway outlet. Two were vegetarian and 4 non-veg. There was no marking(veg/Non veg) on any box, no marking to identify which box had which chicken, sauces, toppings etc. On calling the restaurant the manager's attitude was rude. He replied that you can identify the veg/non-veg salads by just seeing the box and when we asked what about different chicken orders then he had no answer. The paneer in veg salad was stale and tasted nothing like paneer. Very bad service on part of such reputed food chain.
If you are looking for something healthy you should definitely try subway.They use fresh veggies in their subs. Their quality is good and it tastes amazing. It is very healthy.
This used to be the best subway in Gurgaon however in recent times quality has deteriorated. The staff is not very helpful. Sub also lacks taste.

SUBWAY is on the go best food restaurant. 👍 I usually order paneer tikka or chicken tikkka.🐓 I dont know about healthy subs because they put chemicals to make their veggies fresh 😒 Otherwise its always tasty and can fill your tummy 😋

Whenever i get confuse what to order for my lunch this is the place for me. Among other subway this particular, always maintain Good packaging and always delivered on time. So keep up the good work and hope subway improve their service in other restaurants in NCR, who were not able to provide good service to customers.
There was no double filling In the wrap as it was supposed to be.

This is a place i love going. A brand that has created a unique value of its own. Famously known for delivery fresh & healthy Subs, it attracts major people around the brand as a whole. This particular outlet is located on MG Road, Metropolitan Mall & is decently maintained. The service staff here are courteous and respectfully serve the customer. The only thing that i didn't like here was the ill maintained order process. They took lot of time to get the billing done resulting in longer queues. Coming to the food, my favourite here is Chicken Tandoori Sub (its the Sub of the Day on MONDAYs). Great bargain for Rs.140/- with the taste as well. #Follow me on INSTAGRAM for some amazing Food/Travel Blogs    (ID:- Foodiee_Biker)

Subway is my go-to place/option whenever I am extremely hungry and confused about what to eat. Chatpata chana patty, paneer tikka sub, pizziola, veggie delite, Mexican patty sub, hara bhara kebab, aloo patty. all are good options to go for at any subway outlet. One can always rely on subway for a light (actually apt) and yum food.

Good ambiance and tasty food, this is one place which you can think of when you're planning an outing with your family. An exhaustive menu, for both drinks and food makes it even better. My favorites would be the Kastoori Chicken, Tandoori Raan, Dal Makhni and Garlic Naan, and the Gulab Jamun Cheesecake. A place worth visiting, go ahead.

Booked for a party where they Gave us the basement . it was quite spacious though would have loved it if it was more lit. The event went smoothly and the food was nice. Probably would prefer if the breads wouldn't be served in one go. Jeet the manager was very cooperative as well. Full marks

Punjabi by nature is a place known for some good north Indian cuisine. So I visited this place with friends for lunch. It has great ambience and good service to get some delicious food. Things we ordered: Drinks : Barbarian Virgin Mary Main course : Dal Tadka Dal Makhani Lahori Masala Paneer Biryani Butter Roti Butter/Garlic Naan Boondi Raita Desert : Gulaab Jamun  Overall Experience : Ambience 4/5 Service 5/5 Food 4/5 Value for money: 4/5

This Navratri I really wanted to try out Navratri Thali from Punjabi by nature .I went with my husband and we ordered full Navratri Thali. Presentation was good and if I talk about quantity it is good for two person (if they have 4 poori options instead of 2).But all over taste of food was good,not too spicy .Kuttu ki puri with paneer was hit from my side.

This is the place you wanna dine in with your family if you're near Noida. With great ambiance and prompt service you also get some delicious food. I tried their navratra thali and paneer tikka which was way too delicious. You won't feel the absence of onions and garlics. Now you don't have to eat bland food in navratre

I visited this amazing place yesterday to try its navratri menu it has launched recently and I was amazed to see its quality and quantity of dishes present in thali It has makhani paneer, sabudana kheer, sabaudana papadh, stuffed paneer tikka, aloo ki subz, kuttu poori and many more things Also I tried its mocktails and mojitos the best was kashmiri roohafza Also it is famous for its north Indian food and desserts Must visit this place if you really like north indian food Also must go to try its navratri thali
We were on a corporate party . we found cockroaches on the table and in the plate. A big no

We had booked a table for 22 people. Food was bad in taste paneer tikka was saltless, spiceless tasteless. They were constantly serving cold food. Main course was also bad, dal makhani was not good, and the kadhai paneer was also bad It was like naam bade and darshan chote. bahut chote. Such a costly place thats not worth it.

Went to Punjabi 2.0 to try out the famous (and huge) Chole Bhature. The combination was amazing. The green chutney they serve along with the Chole Bathurst is delicious. The service was very prompt. Received the order really quick. Staff was helpful. Try the Chole Bathurst with the onion and chutney it tastes heavenly. Must try !

What we use to eat and what we now get is totally different at PUNJABI BY NATURE. Non-veg platter items were average in taste except the chicken tikkas in it. In main course Butter chicken i ordered was sweet to extreme(order, only if you like sweet butter chicken). Tawa chicken was still better to have with naan and parantha. Staff there is well mannered, polite and was happily serving. P.s- Onion they served in salad was bitter like hell. Sadly i was disappointed here.

Just ordered food from this place, chicken nuggets it was rubbish, soggy in between. I'm going for you MacDonald. This is so disappointing, SHAME ON MACDONALD
Chicken nuggets were really good also the fries were quite crispy and yummy! We also ordered mc aaloo tikki , it tasted really good and fresh! I love this outlet!

My favourite all time joint. Love their wide variety of burgers and wraps. My favourite us spicy paneer wrap which is tangy and spicy to fill my stomach. I love their ice creams too with chocolate syrup on top. Latest mac maharaja burger is also quite a deal to indulge in. Best place to hang with bunch of friends.
Packing charge high otherwise quality perfect
